g.id: When a medical device is labeled as , it signifies that it possesses the inherent capability to fully support the SDC framework, and first implementations using the SDC protocol have been performed. The label signifies full support of the SDC standards. The labels are self-declared - how far and to what extent devices support the SDC protocol must be explained by the self-declaration. SDC ready represents the commitment of the deviceâ€™s manufacturer to embrace and integrate the SDC technology in the future. The labels SDC ready and SDC are issued by the OR.NET association by means of license agreements. It is important to note that achieving 100% SDC capability may not be attainable right now due to the non-final SDC standards.
